        <hl1>On Guns, 'Enough Is Enough'</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Kurt H Miska notes people of Western European democracies live in societies that are not armed to the teeth, and they do not feel their civil rights are being abridged</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It was heartening to see the huge turnout of mothers in Washington to demonstrate against our insane gun culture (front page, May 15). Clearly, something needs to be done to stem the tide of the increasing gun lunacy in this country.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It was heartening to see the huge turnout of mothers in Washington to demonstrate against our insane gun culture (front page, May 15). Clearly, something needs to be done to stem the tide of the increasing gun lunacy in this country.</p>
        <p>I often wonder if the officers and members of the National Rifle Association have ever thought about the fact that the people of Western Europe live in democratic societies that are not armed to the teeth with all manner of what are clearly not sporting weapons. I seriously doubt that these citizens feel that their respective governments are about to abridge their civil rights.</p>
        <p>KURT H. MISKA  Ann Arbor, Mich., May 15, 2000</p>
      </block>
